'''本氏辣酱热狗店'''（{{Lang-en|Ben's Chill Bowl}}）是[[华盛顿哥伦比亚特区|华盛顿特区]]的地标式餐饮店。该店位于[[西北区_(华盛顿特区)|西北区]]的[[U街|U街走廊]]1213号，紧邻林肯剧院。餐厅里供应的辣酱热狗，双拼烟熏热狗和[[奶昔|奶昔]]是当地家喻户晓的美食。这家餐厅自1958年开业后就载入史册。在[[1968年華盛頓哥倫比亞特區大暴動|1968年华盛顿特区大暴动]]期间，警察和抗议者经常光顾此地，安东尼·波登[[安東尼·波登|（Anthony Bourdain）]]和克里斯·塔克[[克里斯·塔克|（Chris Tucker）]]等名人也来过这里品尝美味。

2009年1月，华盛顿特区市长艾德里安·芬提还带着当时的候任总统贝拉克·[[贝拉克·奥巴马|奥巴马]]来到餐厅用餐，欢迎奥巴马来到华盛顿特区。<ref name="Obama">{{Cite news|url=http://blogs.reuters.com/frontrow/2009/01/10/dc-diner-adds-obama-to-list-of-famous-patrons|title=Diner adds Obama to list of famous patrons, Reuters Blogs|publisher=Blogs.reuters.com|date=January 10, 2009|accessdate=July 15, 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090124165931/http://blogs.reuters.com/frontrow/2009/01/10/dc-diner-adds-obama-to-list-of-famous-patrons/|archivedate=January 24, 2009}}</ref>
== 餐厅历史 ==
本氏辣酱热狗店由本恩·阿里和未婚妻维吉尼亚·罗林斯在1958年8月22日一手建立。 <ref name="founded">Ali, Virginia R. (April 3, 1988). "Burned Into the Future; Before April 4, 1968, Washington was a tranquil but segregated town. After the riots, everything changed. Six Washingtonians look back". ''The Washington Post''. p. W28.</ref>阿里是特立尼达裔移民，未婚妻罗林斯是弗吉尼亚州人。当时，阿里在餐厅所在地附近的[[霍华德大学|霍华德大学]]学习牙科学。二人在饭馆开业七周后结婚。 <ref name="obit">{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/story/2009/10/08/ST2009100804374.html?sid=ST2009100804374|title=Ben Ali, 82, Whose Chili Bowl Became a D.C. Landmark, Dies|work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|date=October 9, 2009|accessdate=October 9, 2009|author=Schudel|first=Matt|archive-date=2017-11-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171115143637/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/story/2009/10/08/ST2009100804374.html?sid=ST2009100804374|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite news|title=The Bottomless Bowl of U Street; A Neighborhood Institution Prepares to Celebrate 45 Years of Chili -- and Change|work=The Washington Post|date=August 21, 2003|author=Wilgoren|first=Debbi}}</ref> <ref name="RIPben">{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/10/08/AR2009100804130.html|title=Life Goes On in Rhythm of Ben's|author=Freedom duLac|first=Josh|date=October 9, 2009|work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|pages=A08|accessdate=October 9, 2009|archive-date=2017-11-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171115202800/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/10/08/AR2009100804130.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>     店铺以前是明尼哈哈制片厂的所在地，该厂建于1911年，是华盛顿特区[[无声电影|无声制片厂]]。 <ref name="PBS">[https://www.pbs.org/ellingtonsdc/vtOtherLandMarks.htm#Chili Virtual Duke Ellington's Washington: Tour of Shaw: Ben's Chili Bowl] {{Wayback|url=https://www.pbs.org/ellingtonsdc/vtOtherLandMarks.htm#Chili |date=20201109220003 }}, [[PBS|PBS]]</ref>该建筑是[[U街|大U街历史遗址区的]]一处重要建筑。 <ref>{{Cite web|title=District of Columbia Inventory of Historic Sites|url=http://planning.dc.gov/planning/frames.asp?doc=/planning/lib/planning/New_Inventory_Sep_2004.pdf|accessdate=January 8, 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090130074837/http://planning.dc.gov/planning/frames.asp?doc=%2Fplanning%2Flib%2Fplanning%2FNew_Inventory_Sep_2004.pdf|archivedate=30 January 2009}}</ref>餐厅的大多数摆设都是20世纪50年代留下来的。 <ref name="Globe">Vorhees, Mara, [http://www.boston.com/ae/food/articles/2004/01/28/bens_chili_and_hot_dogs_have_time_tested_appeal/ Ben's chili and hot dogs have time-tested appeal] {{Wayback|url=http://www.boston.com/ae/food/articles/2004/01/28/bens_chili_and_hot_dogs_have_time_tested_appeal/ |date=20160303224738 }}, ''[[The_Boston_Globe|The Boston Globe]]'', 28 January 2004</ref>当时，U街有着“黑人[[百老匯|百老汇]]”的称号。[[艾靈頓公爵|艾灵顿公爵]]、[[邁爾士·戴維斯|麦尔士·戴维斯]]和[[納·京·高爾|纳·京·高尔]]等许多[[爵士乐|爵士乐]]大师在U街酒吧俱乐部演出后都来这家餐厅驻足休息。

1968年，[[馬丁·路德·金恩遇刺案|马丁·路德·金]]在遇刺后，同年4月发生了[[华盛顿大暴动|华盛顿大暴动]]，U街走廊因此遭到严重破坏。<ref name="CNN">[http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0308/22/se.03.html Transcript: Ben's Chili Bowl Celebrates 45th Anniversary] {{Wayback|url=http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0308/22/se.03.html |date=20191222093743 }}, [[CNN|CNN]], aired 22 August 2003</ref>在暴动期间，美国学生非暴力协调委员会的主席黑人激进分子斯托克利·卡迈克尔要求本氏辣酱热狗店在此期间继续营业，阿里的餐厅因此获得了宵禁后营业的许可。这家餐厅招待过维护当地治安的警官和消防员，还有黑人激进分子。暴力和纵火事件愈演愈烈，本恩不得不在门脸上写上“黑人兄弟的餐厅”，以防暴徒袭击。<ref name="BusinessWeek">{{Cite news|url=http://www.businessweek.com/magazine/content/05_49/b3962460.htm|title=Ben Ali's Way|author=Kamal Ali as told to Gay Jervey|work=[[BusinessWeek|BusinessWeek]]|date=Winter 2005|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080504164359/http://www.businessweek.com/magazine/content/05_49/b3962460.htm|archivedate=2008-05-04}}</ref>

[[File:Bens-chili-bowl.jpg|左]]
许多店铺都遭到了破坏，当地的居民逃到了郊区居住。从20世纪70年代中期到80年代，当地的经济处于下滑状态。这个地区成为了著名的瘾君子聚集地，辣酱热狗店将店内员工裁减到只剩下一人。<ref name="CNN">[http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0308/22/se.03.html Transcript: Ben's Chili Bowl Celebrates 45th Anniversary], [[CNN|CNN]], aired 22 August 2003</ref>本恩和维吉尼亚的儿子卡马尔回忆道：“我们留在了这里，餐厅还有一批老顾客，因为这家店就像当地的理发店一样不可或缺。顾客坐在店里谈天说地。这里一直像家一样，当地居民保护着自己的家。”<ref name="BusinessWeek">{{Cite news|url=http://www.businessweek.com/magazine/content/05_49/b3962460.htm|title=Ben Ali's Way|author=Kamal Ali as told to Gay Jervey|work=[[BusinessWeek|BusinessWeek]]|date=Winter 2005|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080504164359/http://www.businessweek.com/magazine/content/05_49/b3962460.htm|archivedate=2008-05-04}}</ref>店内停止供应深受瘾君子喜爱的派和蛋糕，同时，警察也会在楼上的窗户实时监控毒贩的行踪。<ref name="obit">{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/story/2009/10/08/ST2009100804374.html?sid=ST2009100804374|title=Ben Ali, 82, Whose Chili Bowl Became a D.C. Landmark, Dies|work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|date=October 9, 2009|accessdate=October 9, 2009|author=Schudel|first=Matt}}</ref>

餐厅对面的U街地铁站扩建工程于1991年完成，这让当时开业的许多餐厅不得不歇业关门，但是本氏辣酱热狗店仍开门迎客，来招待扩建工程的建筑工人。<ref name="Globe">Vorhees, Mara, [http://www.boston.com/ae/food/articles/2004/01/28/bens_chili_and_hot_dogs_have_time_tested_appeal/ Ben's chili and hot dogs have time-tested appeal], ''[[The_Boston_Globe|The Boston Globe]]'', 28 January 2004</ref> [[华盛顿邮报|《华盛顿邮报》]]评论，本氏辣酱热狗店“可能是唯一一家在1968年暴动发生和华盛顿[[華盛頓地鐵綠線|地铁绿线]]建设之后能幸免于难的饭馆”。<ref name="WaPo">Becton, Neal, [https://web.archive.org/web/20180924134727/https://www.washingtonpost.com/ac2/wp-dyn/?node=cityguide%2Fprofile&id=792153 City Guide: Ben's Chili Bowl], ''[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]'' editorial review</ref>地铁站的建成，犯罪率的下降也让当地经济逐渐复兴，中产阶层人群逐渐增多。从20世纪90年代初期开始，餐厅的收入每年增长10%，2005年达到150万美元，店内的员工数量逐步增长，2005年达到了20人。<ref name="BusinessWeek">{{Cite news|url=http://www.businessweek.com/magazine/content/05_49/b3962460.htm|title=Ben Ali's Way|author=Kamal Ali as told to Gay Jervey|work=[[BusinessWeek|BusinessWeek]]|date=Winter 2005|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080504164359/http://www.businessweek.com/magazine/content/05_49/b3962460.htm|archivedate=2008-05-04}}</ref>

[[File:Grill_at_Ben's_Chili_Bowl.jpg|缩略图]]
2007年夏天，本氏热狗店店长作为中间人参与协商十家当地小型企业和能源公司的能源转换项目，准备将消耗能源全部转换成风能。<ref name="wind">{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/08/15/business/15wind.html |title=Kennedy, Shawn G., "Washington's small businesses tap into green power," The New York Post, August 15, 2007. |access-date=2021-01-11 |archive-date=2021-02-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210227105413/https://www.nytimes.com/2007/08/15/business/15wind.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[紐約郵報|《纽约邮报》]]援引尼扎姆·阿里的话说：“我们认为这个想法有助于社区和城市发展、环境保护。事实证明，对于所有人来说，这个想法具有经济效益”。 

2008年，本氏辣酱热狗店在新建的[[國民球場|国民球场]]地区开了第一家分店<ref>{{Cite web|title=Ben's Chili Bowl News|url=http://www.benschilibowl.com/news.html|accessdate=May 26, 2008|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080731214854/http://www.benschilibowl.com/news.html|archivedate=July 31, 2008}}</ref>，但分店只提供总店菜单内的部分食物。本恩于2009年10月7日逝世，享年82岁。<ref name="bizjournal">{{Cite news|url=http://washington.bizjournals.com/washington/stories/2009/10/05/daily83.html|title=Ben's Chili Bowl owner dies|author=Frederick|first=Missy|date=October 8, 2009|work=[[American_City_Business_Journals|Washington Business Journal]]|publisher=washington.bizjournals.com|accessdate=October 8, 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091011105341/http://washington.bizjournals.com/washington/stories/2009/10/05/daily83.html|archivedate=11 October 2009}}</ref>本恩和妻子维吉尼亚将饭馆的日常照料工作交给了儿子卡马尔和尼扎姆后，老两口决定退休。本恩·阿里的哀悼活动在城市的各个角落以不同的形式进行。其中，市长艾德里安·芬提写了一封悼词：“听闻本氏辣酱热狗店创始人逝世，我深表痛心。本恩以自己的名字命名这家餐厅，并一手创立哥伦比亚特区奉为至宝的本氏辣酱热狗店。本恩·阿里为餐厅投入毕生心血。餐厅历经腥风血雨，成为城市之灵魂，人民之骄傲”。<ref>[http://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local-beat/Ben-Ali-Dead-at-82-63763567.html Stabley, Matthew, "Ben's chili bowl owner dead at 82: Ben's is a Washington landmark," NBCWashington.com, Oct 8, 2009.]</ref>2009年，本恩的儿子卡马尔和尼扎姆在餐厅原址附近位于西北地区U街1211号开了“本恩邻家菜”，这家餐厅是提供酒水的高档餐厅。<ref name="WT">{{Cite web |url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2009/jun/17/drinks-flow-next-door |title="Drinks flow next door at Ben's, The Washington Times. |access-date=2021-01-11 |archive-date=2020-08-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200818094447/https://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2009/jun/17/drinks-flow-next-door/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>尼扎姆说，这家餐厅主打酒水饮料，来弥补本氏辣酱热狗店的不足，餐厅经营目标就是“保持初心”。这家饭馆会从11点开店到闭店提供辣酱热狗店菜单上的所有食物，除此之外，还拥有自己的午餐、晚餐和夜宵菜单。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Bensnextdoor.com.|url=http://www.bensnextdoor.com/ordereze/default.aspx|accessdate=2011-01-10|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110117184744/http://www.bensnextdoor.com/ordereze/default.aspx|archivedate=2011-01-17}}</ref>[[File:Chili_half_smoke_Bens.jpg|缩略图]]

== 顾客和认可度 ==
[[File:Bush_mural_-_ben's_chili_bowl_(cropped).jpg|左]]]]
[[波士頓環球報|《波士顿环球报》]]称，从[[龐克文化|朋克]]打扮的青年到穿着时尚的商务人士，本氏热狗店的顾客遍及各行各业。<ref name="Globe">Vorhees, Mara, [http://www.boston.com/ae/food/articles/2004/01/28/bens_chili_and_hot_dogs_have_time_tested_appeal/ Ben's chili and hot dogs have time-tested appeal], ''[[The_Boston_Globe|The Boston Globe]]'', 28 January 2004</ref>2001年，本恩和维吉尼亚的儿子卡马尔对于顾客发生变化这件事发表了自己的看法：“你能听到顾客对食物做出评价，甚至有的白人顾客认为自己吃了辣酱热狗才是最时髦的人。现在他们看到店里还有许多其他的白人也来到这里吃饭，就有点闷闷不乐。”<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.independent.co.uk/world/americas/article226978.ece|title=City Life: Washington|first=Andrew|author=Buncombe|work=[[The_Independent|The Independent]]|date=June 4, 2001|accessdate=October 1, 2010}}{{Dead link|date=November 2016|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref>

