最有名的老顾客要属喜剧演员[[比爾·寇司比|比尔·科斯比]] ，他带着自己的未婚妻来店里约会。<ref name="PBS">[https://www.pbs.org/ellingtonsdc/vtOtherLandMarks.htm#Chili Virtual Duke Ellington's Washington: Tour of Shaw: Ben's Chili Bowl], [[PBS|PBS]]</ref>寇司比回忆道，1958年那时，自己是个海军，军队驻扎在[[贝塞斯达_(马里兰州)|马里兰州贝塞斯达]]，自己经常光顾U街的爵士俱乐部，第一次成为餐饮店的老顾客。<ref name="BC">{{Cite web |url=http://homeincomekit.org/be-your-own-boss/bens-chili-bowl-u-st-nw |title=Alexander, Keith L., "Ben's Celebrates Chili Power," Washington Post, August 21, 2008. |access-date=2021-01-11 |archive-date=2020-07-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200726193027/http://homeincomekit.org/be-your-own-boss/bens-chili-bowl-u-st-nw |dead-url=yes }}</ref>他还说，和[[馬里蘭大學學院市分校|马里兰大学]]学生卡米尔一起来这里吃饭的几次中，“每次都能吃六个双拼烟熏热狗”。1985年，寇司比在本氏热狗店举行新闻发布会，来庆祝自己电视情景喜剧[[考斯比一家|《考斯比一家》]]大获成功。<ref name="Globe">Vorhees, Mara, [http://www.boston.com/ae/food/articles/2004/01/28/bens_chili_and_hot_dogs_have_time_tested_appeal/ Ben's chili and hot dogs have time-tested appeal], ''[[The_Boston_Globe|The Boston Globe]]'', 28 January 2004</ref>从那以后，他一到华盛顿区就去店里坐坐，吃几个双拼烟熏热狗。店里的一个告示上写着：“只有比尔·寇司比可以吃霸王餐”。<ref name="BenPol">{{Cite web|title=Ben's Policy|url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/staple/1000067716|accessdate=December 18, 2007|date=August 3, 2007|work=Flickr|archive-date=2020-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200726192441/https://www.flickr.com/photos/staple/1000067716|dead-url=no}}</ref>2008年11月3日，店里又贴了新的告示：奥巴马家的人可以免费享用本店的食物。<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Election Comes to Ben's Chili Bowl|url=http://dcist.com/2008/11/04/the_election_comes_to_bens_chili_bo.php|accessdate=July 15, 2009|date=November 4, 2008|publisher=DCist|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090125005924/http://dcist.com/2008/11/04/the_election_comes_to_bens_chili_bo.php|archivedate=January 25, 2009}}</ref>从2012年开始，店内的墙上就画上寇司比的巨幅壁画。不过，2017年1月，寇司比面临性侵犯指控后，壁画就撤了下来。<ref name="Ben's_Deletes_Cosby">{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/local/wp/2017/01/26/bens-chili-bowl-paints-over-its-mural-of-bill-cosby-and-obama/|title=Ben's Chili Bowl paints over its mural of Bill Cosby — and Obama|work=The Washington Post|date=January 26, 2017|accessdate=January 26, 2017|archive-date=2018-10-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181010012639/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/local/wp/2017/01/26/bens-chili-bowl-paints-over-its-mural-of-bill-cosby-and-obama/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

[[克里斯·塔克|克里斯·塔克]]和[[博诺|波诺]]等其他名人在这几年里也光顾了这家店。2005年，新闻记者泰德·坎培尔卸任新闻节目[[夜線|夜线]]的主持工作后，在这家餐厅里举办了欢送会。<ref name="obit">{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/story/2009/10/08/ST2009100804374.html?sid=ST2009100804374|title=Ben Ali, 82, Whose Chili Bowl Became a D.C. Landmark, Dies|work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|date=October 9, 2009|accessdate=October 9, 2009|author=Schudel|first=Matt}}</ref>2009年1月10日，时任候选总统的[[贝拉克·奥巴马|贝拉克·奥巴马]]来本氏热狗店就餐。<ref name="Obama">{{Cite news|url=http://blogs.reuters.com/frontrow/2009/01/10/dc-diner-adds-obama-to-list-of-famous-patrons|title=Diner adds Obama to list of famous patrons, Reuters Blogs|publisher=Blogs.reuters.com|date=January 10, 2009|accessdate=July 15, 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090124165931/http://blogs.reuters.com/frontrow/2009/01/10/dc-diner-adds-obama-to-list-of-famous-patrons/|archivedate=January 24, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/americas/7822643.stm|title=BBC video of Obama at the restaurant|work=BBC News|date=January 11, 2009|accessdate=July 15, 2009|archive-date=2009-02-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090217021224/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/americas/7822643.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref>  

[[华盛顿邮报|《华盛顿邮报》]]称：“截止20世纪90年代，想参与竞选的议员都来本氏热狗店吃过饭”。<ref name="obit">{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/story/2009/10/08/ST2009100804374.html?sid=ST2009100804374|title=Ben Ali, 82, Whose Chili Bowl Became a D.C. Landmark, Dies|work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|date=October 9, 2009|accessdate=October 9, 2009|author=Schudel|first=Matt}}</ref>安东尼·威廉姆斯在成功竞选市长后，立即来到了本氏辣酱热狗店。<ref name="sietsema">{{Cite web|title=The 2004 James Beard Foundation Gallo of Sonoma America’s Classics Awards|url=http://www.jamesbeard.org/about/press/newsdetails.php?news_id=48|accessdate=October 24, 2009|author=Sietsema|date=May 10, 2004|first=Tom|work=The James Beard Foundation|publisher=([[Internet_Archive|web.archive.org]])|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080203080925/http://www.jamesbeard.org/about/press/newsdetails.php?news_id=48|archivedate=February 3, 2008}}</ref><ref>Description written by Tom Sietsema, writer for ''[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]'', and member of The James Beard Foundation Restaurant Awards Committee</ref>但是，来到本氏热狗店的就餐的还有外国友人。1998年，前华盛顿特区市长马里恩·巴里描述称，自己曾到[[加纳|加纳]]会见霍华德大学的校友阿克拉市长。阿拉克市长见到我第一句说的就是，“很高兴你能来到阿克拉，本氏热狗店还开张吗？”<ref>{{Cite news|title=For 40 Years, the Hottest Place in Town|first=Allan|author=Lengel|work=The Washington Post|date=August 21, 1998|page=C1}}</ref>据报道，2010年3月，法国总统[[尼古拉·萨科齐|尼古拉·萨科奇]]和他的妻子[[卡拉·布鲁尼·萨科齐|卡拉·布鲁尼·萨科齐]]在拜访华盛顿特区时，来到了本氏热狗店用餐，每个人吃了两个双拼烟熏热狗。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/03/30/sarkozys-eat-half-smokes-at-bens-chili-bowl |title=Cooper, Helene, "Sarkozys eat half-smokes at Ben's," The Caucus, March 30, 2010. |access-date=2021-01-11 |archive-date=2021-03-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210311045257/https://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/03/30/sarkozys-eat-half-smokes-at-bens-chili-bowl/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[File:Borf_Loves_Bens.jpg|左]]
《塘鹅暗杀令》<ref name="GWU">[http://www.gwu.edu/~jazz/venuesm.html Historic U Street Jazz: The Minnehaha Theatre / Ben's Chili Bowl] {{Wayback|url=http://www.gwu.edu/~jazz/venuesm.html |date=20201019084710 }}, [[George_Washington_University|George Washington University]]</ref>和[[絕對陰謀|《玩耍状态》]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/04/10/AR2009041000056.html|title=On the Set of 'State of Play': Washington Post Consultant Tells (Almost) All|work=The Washington Post|date=April 12, 2009|accessdate=July 15, 2009|first=R.B.|author=Brenner|archive-date=2019-10-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191027145456/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/04/10/AR2009041000056.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>等电影在这家餐厅取景，餐厅还登上了“数十个电视节目”。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/postmortem/2009/10/how_i_got_the_story_ben_ali_of.html |title=Schudel, Matt, "How I got the story: Ben of Ben's Chili Bowl," WashingtonPost.com, October 9, 2009. |access-date=2021-01-11 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304112826/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/postmortem/2009/10/how_i_got_the_story_ben_ali_of.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>短片《本恩的早餐》中几乎所有场景都在餐厅拍摄。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Ben's World|url=http://www.washingtoncitypaper.com/articles/19638/bens-world/|accessdate=31 March 2011|author=Anderson|first=Brett|work=Washington City Paper|publisher=Washington City Paper|archive-date=2016-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303194122/http://www.washingtoncitypaper.com/articles/19638/bens-world/|dead-url=no}}</ref>2019年，关于种族主义的纪录片《美国黑人公路旅行指南》将这家餐厅设为主要取景地。不仅如此，在许多小说里，这家餐厅成为了碰面地点，比如乔治·佩勒卡诺斯所著的《萨克曼国王》。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.hachettebookgroup.com/features/georgepelecanos/washington |title=Website for George Pelecanos. |access-date=2021-01-11 |archive-date=2017-08-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170809101413/http://www.hachettebookgroup.com/features/georgepelecanos/washington/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

